l, or try a thicker line in the base texture, maybe with a gradient on the edge so any averaging becomes less noticable at distance.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2021-06-11T03:36:15.016Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":24,"readers_count":23,"score":9.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":6888,"topic_slug":"textures-blurring-in-short-distance-anisotropy","display_username":"SirNate0","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":628,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":42919,"name":"evol","username":"evolgames","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/evolgames/{size}/3169_2.png","created_at":"2021-06-11T03:59:53.159Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eOh okay. Well the materials has a\u003cbr\u003e\nsingle simple PNG texture so no mip mapping is set. Is Urho auto-generating them? I recall some automipmap export function in Gimp. Maybe thatâ€™ll help\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2021-06-11T03:59:53.159Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":24,"readers_count":23,"score":4.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":6888,"topic_slug":"textures-blurring-in-short-distance-anisotropy","display_username":"evol","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"SirNate0","name":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1292,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":42920,"name":"Yao Wei Tjong","username":"weitjong","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/weitjong/{size}/4_2.png","created_at":"2021-06-11T04:30:19.604Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHave you tried to disable the mipmap? You can create a matching xml file at the same resource folder where your PNG is being loaded from, and specify extra instructions there. See example usage in the UI.png and UI.xml from the Urho3D project provided texture folder.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2021-06-11T04:31:33.642Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":24,"readers_count":23,"score":4.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":6888,"topic_slug":"textures-blurring-in-short-distance-anisotropy","display_username":"Yao Wei Tjong","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Admin","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":4,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":42922,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2021-06-11T09:24:50.060Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"evolgames\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"6888\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/evolgames/40/3169_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e evolgames:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIâ€™m not sure if it is a mip map, anisotropy, or texture filtering\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTL;DR: Increase anisotropy until you like how it looks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBoth trilinear texture filtering (filtering between different mips) and anisotropy contribute to this behaviour.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you have anisotropy off (anisotropy=1), rasterizer will always pick smallest mip level. I.e. if you squish 1024x1024 texture vertically 4 times (via scale, or due to projection), rasterizer will use 256x256 mip level. It introduces unnecessary blur along largest axis (x axis in your case). Rasterizer \u003cstrong\u003ehas\u003c/strong\u003e to pick smallest mip level because otherwise there will be noise on the smallest axis (y axis in your case).\u003cbr\u003e\nSo, if you disable mips or mip filtering, you will get less blur and more noise.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you want to have less blur without having any noise, you have to increate anisotropy level. In the example above, rasterizer will work as if sampling 1024x256 texture (if anisotropy=4): rasterizer will remove noise without any unwanted blur. It will cost you some performace of course.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2021-06-11T09:25:34.762Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":23,"readers_count":22,"score":9.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":6888,"topic_slug":"textures-blurring-in-short-distance-anisotropy","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":42923,"name":"evol","username":"evolgames","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/evolgames/{size}/3169_2.png","created_at":"2021-06-11T14:12:13.806Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eOk so hereâ€™s what it looks like with this texture xml:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;texture\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;filter mode=\"nearestanisotropic\" anisotropy=\"4\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;mipmap enable=\"false\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;quality high=\"2\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/texture\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/0/0aa6be24c40d3e583a37f248f0806b13661587e0.png\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/1we1cyvkra7wUQliBLZyzGJaQkU.png?dl=1\" title=\"Screenshot_2021-06-11_10-08-05\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/0/0aa6be24c40d3e583a37f248f0806b13661587e0_2_690x388.png\" alt=\"Screenshot_2021-06-11_10-08-05\" data-base62-sha1=\"1we1cyvkra7wUQliBLZyzGJaQkU\" width=\"690\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/0/0aa6be24c40d3e583a37f248f0806b13661587e0_2_690x388.png, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/0/0aa6be24c40d3e583a37f248f0806b13661587e0_2_1035x582.png 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/0/0aa6be24c40d3e583a37f248f0806b13661587e0_2_1380x776.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/0/0aa6be24c40d3e583a37f248f0806b13661587e0_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eScreenshot_2021-06-11_10-08-05\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1920Ã—1080 152 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand with mipmaps enabled\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/d/d5388beba7715bbe2045ef7038352ac8070b3a29.png\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/uqeQNMLI0HwyEhHFXZe0rjZxjrH.png?dl=1\" title=\"Screenshot_2021-06-11_10-08-49\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/d/d5388beba7715bbe2045ef7038352ac8070b3a29_2_690x388.png\" alt=\"Screenshot_2021-06-11_10-08-49\" data-base62-sha1=\"uqeQNMLI0HwyEhHFXZe0rjZxjrH\" width=\"690\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/d/d5388beba7715bbe2045ef7038352ac8070b3a29_2_690x388.png, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/d/d5388beba7715bbe2045ef7038352ac8070b3a29_2_1035x582.png 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/d/d5388beba7715bbe2045ef7038352ac8070b3a29_2_1380x776.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/d/d5388beba7715bbe2045ef7038352ac8070b3a29_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eScreenshot_2021-06-11_10-08-49\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1920Ã—1080 161 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI see what you mean about noise. I should note that no textures are squeezed or stretched, all are on 1x1x1 cubes. Looks like switching from trilinear to nearestanisotropic was what made the most difference in my case.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2021-06-11T14:33:29.597Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":22,"readers_count":21,"score":9.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":6888,"topic_slug":"textures-blurring-in-short-distance-anisotropy","display_username":"evol","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/0/0aa6be24c40d3e583a37f248f0806b13661587e0.png","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"0aa6be24c40d3e583a37f248f0806b13661587e0.png","clicks":0},{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/d/d5388beba7715bbe2045ef7038352ac8070b3a29.png","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"d5388beba7715bbe2045ef7038352ac8070b3a29.png","clicks":0},{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/smeared-tiled-texture-when-looking-parallel-to-it/6927/4","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"